      "title": "I will always listen to my constituents, even if we may not...",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Tay2019/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-1/cp0/c20.0.50.50a/p50x50/118284446_1181187205597451_4408149288731870177_o.jpg?_nc_cat=102\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=m3IJEaWfp1AAX8owTVw\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-2.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ae50f33dffe903ce6d274a6e2f76ccea\u0026oe=5FD0DA1E\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Tay2019/\"\u003eDenver School Board Director - Tay Anderson\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Tay2019/posts/1238141939901977\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com\"\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eI will always listen to my constituents, even if we may not agree.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/photo.php\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/v/l/t1.0-0/p526x296/123195095_10221014890174660_177929318653224602_o.jpg?_nc_cat=105\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=8024bb\u0026_nc_ohc=7Svy5IDVV5oAX9kcEBq\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-2.fna\u0026tp=6\u0026oh=41847d5b3c00c05c650dc09a433f84d2\u0026oe=5FD1A196\" alt=\"Image may contain: one or more people\" width=\"526\" height=\"347\" caption=\"Image may contain: one or more people\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/photo.php\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-0/p235x165/123287539_10221014890774675_8820362809670108834_o.jpg?_nc_cat=106\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=8024bb\u0026_nc_ohc=iaWaCSJaGDEAX_QQ-6L\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=6\u0026oh=bb8979425fed4255067b0c65daff03cd\u0026oe=5FD02CCD\" alt=\"Image may contain: one or more people, people standing and outdoor\" width=\"252\" height=\"165\" caption=\"Image may contain: one or more people, people standing and outdoor\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/photo.php\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-0/p173x172/123198631_10221014890494668_1409055466110438031_o.jpg?_nc_cat=105\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=8024bb\u0026_nc_ohc=L7zCNbPOoJoAX8DkCPw\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-2.fna\u0026tp=6\u0026oh=37a127395e02191b211acc9f6124c5ef\u0026oe=5FD0B465\" alt=\"Image may contain: one or more people and outdoor\" width=\"254\" height=\"172\" caption=\"Image may contain: one or more people and outdoor\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003eDave Russell is with Tay Anderson.\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/dave.russell.961/posts/10221014895454792\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com\"\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/istandwithtay\"\u003e#IStandWithTay\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e A group of parents protested in front of the DPS admin building Friday afternoon. They were demanding DPS schools open immediately for in-person ...learning. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e Director Tay Anderson was out there listening to these DPS parents. He wasn’t endorsing their position. But he was listening.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e If there were other DPS board members or any DPS administrators there, I missed seeing them. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e Every time Tay is out in public, his safety and his life is at risk. It is an act of courage EVERY time he shows up for the community. And he always shows up. Let's make sure we always have his back.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/family\"\u003e#family\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com\"\u003eSee More\u003c/a\u003e",
